==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nickelous
<hw>Nick"el*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, those compounds of nickel in
which, as contrasted with the <contr>nickelic</contr> compounds, the
metal has a lower valence; <as>as, <ex>nickelous</ex> oxide</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Frankland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nickel steel</ent>⟦br⟧
